WEBVTT

00:00.034 --> 00:03.700
The following message by Alistair Begg is made available by Truth For Life.

00:04.501 --> 00:08.467
For more information, visit us online at truthforlife.org.

00:10.049 --> 00:19.163
Well, from verse 11 to 16, command and teach these things.

00:20.084 --> 00:29.138
Let no one despise you for your youth, but set the believers an example in speech, in conduct, in love, in faith,

00:29.442 --> 00:30.243
in purity.

00:31.505 --> 00:36.951
Until I come, devote yourself to the public reading of Scripture, to exhortation, to teaching.

00:38.133 --> 00:45.783
Do not neglect the gift you have, which was given you by prophecy when the council of elders laid their hands on you.

00:46.804 --> 00:52.651
Practice these things, immerse yourself in them, so that all may see your progress.

00:53.733 --> 00:56.476
Keep a close watch on yourself and on the teaching.

00:56.997 --> 00:58.098
Persisten this.

00:58.370 --> 01:05.260
for by so doing, you will save both yourself and your heroes."

01:05.280 --> 01:15.734
Well, Father, we thank You for Your continued gracious presence by the Holy Spirit among us in the events of the day.

01:15.754 --> 01:24.126
You assembled us, not in a haphazard way, but purposefully, that You have plans and purposes for us.

01:24.206 --> 01:26.930
You have good deeds for ordained for us to do.

01:27.586 --> 01:32.954
and we offer ourselves to you as we come to the formal end of our time together.

01:33.755 --> 01:45.192
And we pray that we might always be help and never a hindrance to one another as we seek to follow Christ in whose name we pray, Amen.

01:47.376 --> 01:57.010
Well, I think it's fairly straightforward to say that if someone had asked Timothy if he could summarize the exhortation that was coming to him,

01:57.122 --> 02:07.599
hear from Paul in this fourth chapter, indeed, through the whole letter, perhaps, he would have said, well, I would answer by repeating verse 16.

02:08.260 --> 02:12.306
Keep a close watch on yourself and on the teaching.

02:13.007 --> 02:17.875
He said, I hear this sounding out clearly from the apostle's pen.

02:19.077 --> 02:24.946
Or in J.B. Phillips' paraphrase, keep a critical eye, both upon your own life

02:25.218 --> 02:26.961
and in the teaching you give.

02:27.001 --> 02:29.404
It's a good word, isn't it?

02:29.585 --> 02:31.648
Critical I on your own life.

02:32.209 --> 02:37.116
Not a critical I on the person up the street's life, that's not your problem or mine.

02:37.156 --> 02:42.024
In the NIV, watch your life and doctrine closely.

02:43.586 --> 02:51.218
Now, we began by noticing that the context in which this was taking place was one of the potential for apostasy

02:51.618 --> 02:54.543
We also acknowledge that the letter is a personal letter.

02:54.643 --> 02:59.271
It is written to Timothy, but that it would also have a public reading.

03:00.513 --> 03:14.738
And so in learning what Paul expects of Timothy, the congregations who were in the hearing of this material were also learning what to expect of their pastor.

03:15.170 --> 03:17.694
I always found it one of the very difficult things to do.

03:18.174 --> 03:24.864
I felt very vulnerable when going through material like this in front of the congregation because there is nowhere to hide.

03:25.685 --> 03:30.472
They know who you are, especially if you've been there for any length of time and so on.

03:31.133 --> 03:38.503
And when you read these passages, they learn what it is legitimate for them to expect of their pastor.

03:39.325 --> 03:43.090
So if it's challenging to read, as it were, in the privacy of our own home,

03:43.234 --> 03:48.601
It's actually even more challenging to read it out in the public forum of the church.

03:50.062 --> 03:59.374
And Paul is aware of the challenge Timothy faces in fulfilling this, and he is to command and teach these things.

04:00.295 --> 04:02.198
It's a very straightforward sentence, isn't it?

04:02.818 --> 04:07.324
This exhortation actually comes eight times in the course of this letter.

04:08.626 --> 04:12.210
And what is he supposed to be conveying?

04:12.450 --> 04:25.150
Well, if you like, he has been charged, and some of you, we haven't spoken about this, but some of you were doubtless in the military, and in the military, you were familiar with being, giving your standing orders.

04:25.651 --> 04:38.911
And the standing orders are, quote, a military order outlining overruling that is retained irrespective of changing conditions.

04:39.432 --> 04:40.594
A military order

04:41.314 --> 04:45.218
overruling, nah, I can't read my own writing.

04:45.719 --> 04:52.326
It's a military order that is retained, whatever that word was, irrespective of changing conditions.

04:53.126 --> 04:59.853
Incidentally, violating my own material here, if you'd prepared properly, you would know what that word was, and you would have fixed it.

05:00.474 --> 05:04.438
But it's easy to tell others what to do, it's much harder to do it yourself.

05:05.259 --> 05:08.082
Now, from the outset of the letter, he sounded out the note,

05:08.418 --> 05:12.582
to the question that my Scottish brother raised.

05:13.323 --> 05:17.247
What do we do in terms of confront confrontation and so on?

05:17.808 --> 05:35.826
Verse 3 of chapter 1, as I urged you when I was going to Macedonia, remain at Ephesus so that you may charge certain persons not to teach any different doctrine, nor to devote themselves to myths and endless genealogies and so on.

05:36.962 --> 05:48.880
to be prepared as a young pastor to say, you mustn't believe that, and as a young pastor to say, and you must believe this.

05:49.921 --> 05:52.325
That's what he's actually urging him to.

05:53.006 --> 05:57.172
And he recognizes the challenge that comes to him as a younger man.

05:57.232 --> 06:06.866
Now, it's speculation, but the chances are that Timothy may have been in his 30s, maybe even approaching 40.

06:07.234 --> 06:10.819
So we shouldn't imagine that he's a teenager like some of the disciples.

06:11.660 --> 06:15.906
But youthfulness brings its own challenges.

06:17.968 --> 06:36.914
The challenge a young minister is often prone to try to attain by one jump and to jump to the height that others have reached by a long series of jumps over a long period of time.

06:37.538 --> 06:39.982
When we're young, we're impatient.

06:40.623 --> 06:46.492
We overestimate what we can accomplish in a year, we underestimate what we can accomplish in five years.

06:47.373 --> 07:03.858
We also have predilections that are part and parcel of youthfulness, the desire for power, the desire for possessions, the desire for prestige, the longing to fulfill our passions and so on.

07:04.322 --> 07:07.987
And so Paul understands all of this and more besides.

07:08.808 --> 07:17.521
And he wants it to be absolutely clear that Timothy needs to, if we might say, get ahold of himself.

07:18.842 --> 07:25.812
The danger is when you're young to try and cover for your youthfulness, I say this to my shame, really.

07:25.832 --> 07:32.722
The temptation is to become bossy, perhaps, or to become very hortatory.

07:32.930 --> 07:51.536
constantly saying, come on, come on, and urging people, or to become authoritarian, or to try and make emphasis by dint of personality, or by our use of volume, or whatever it might be.

07:51.576 --> 07:58.306
All of these things we need to guard against always, because that's not why we're there.

07:58.987 --> 08:01.170
Timothy, this is what you are to do.

08:01.378 --> 08:07.427
command and teach these things and don't let people look down on you because you're young.

08:07.467 --> 08:14.337
I was very young when I was ordained to the gospel ministry in 1976.

08:14.577 --> 08:18.042
If I was born in 52, that means I was 24.

08:19.304 --> 08:24.893
And I didn't look very old at 24.

08:24.933 --> 08:28.658
In fact, I didn't even look 24.

08:29.250 --> 08:34.717
And it was not something that was immediately appealing to anybody at all.

08:35.198 --> 08:57.586
I remember on one occasion in the early days, Derek Prime sent me to a hospital to visit a lady who was the wife of a doctor, a prominent heart surgeon in Glasgow called Philip Caves, who tragically died of a heart attack himself after playing squash at the age of 39.

08:58.114 --> 09:01.938
And it was anyway, that's just an aside.

09:02.338 --> 09:06.202
But so I didn't know him or his wife, but I was sent to visit.

09:06.782 --> 09:10.105
And when I got to the hospital in the ward, she was asleep.

09:10.986 --> 09:11.907
And sleep in the bed.

09:12.427 --> 09:16.752
So I just sat on the end of the bed.

09:17.833 --> 09:23.097
And she came to, and she saw me, and she said, who are you?

09:23.118 --> 09:27.922
And I said, well, I'm the assistant to the pastor.

09:28.450 --> 09:30.812
And she said, but you're a boy.

09:30.873 --> 09:33.395
But you're a boy.

09:33.415 --> 09:38.441
And I followed saying, yeah, yeah, yeah.

09:38.941 --> 09:41.404
My first funeral and I wore a clerical collar.

09:42.285 --> 09:42.745
I had to.

09:42.765 --> 09:43.826
That was the rule.

09:44.627 --> 09:50.093
When I walked out in that crematorium, I mean, people thought it was Saturday Night Live.

09:51.114 --> 09:55.058
This cannot be the thing.

09:55.138 --> 10:01.528
So I'm very susceptible to the idea of having people look down on me because of my youth.

10:01.889 --> 10:05.514
What he's saying is, don't have them look down on you because you're just young.

10:06.035 --> 10:09.621
Have them look up to you because you're an example to them.

10:10.542 --> 10:12.145
That's what he's actually saying.

10:13.146 --> 10:20.658
People won't despise your youthfulness, Timothy, if you give them an example to admire and to follow.

10:21.378 --> 10:25.302
So the answer to our youthfulness is not saying, oh, no, I'm much older than you think.

10:25.642 --> 10:26.843
And I'm much more, and so on.

10:26.863 --> 10:27.484
No, no.

10:27.504 --> 10:32.388
No, just make sure that you train yourself for godliness.

10:34.470 --> 10:38.094
And let me tell you where you should concentrate.

10:38.134 --> 10:40.736
Number one, speech.

10:41.637 --> 10:43.139
Speech makes perfect sense.

10:43.619 --> 10:45.140
You're going to be a preacher or a teacher.

10:45.441 --> 10:46.602
You're going to use your mouth.

10:47.142 --> 10:51.026
Make sure then that your speech is true.

10:51.298 --> 10:54.582
It's kind, it's purposefully helpful.

10:56.024 --> 11:03.254
Remember that we used to say at school, at least in Scotland, sticks and stones will break your bones, but names will never hurt you.

11:04.636 --> 11:05.017
Rubbish.

11:05.878 --> 11:06.238
Rubbish.

11:06.979 --> 11:13.148
You can recover from sticks and stones, but words, words have tremendous power.

11:14.209 --> 11:20.818
And words fitly spoken are like apples of gold in, you know, frames of silver.

11:21.282 --> 11:26.890
But words that come from a tongue, James mentions it again, doesn't he?

11:27.651 --> 11:31.036
Because your tongue, he says, it's a deadly thing.

11:31.056 --> 11:32.739
It's full of restless evil.

11:33.700 --> 11:38.527
And it is the kind of thing that can do tremendous damage.

11:39.468 --> 11:40.810
It is an irony, isn't it?

11:41.231 --> 11:48.882
More than that, that when Isaiah is confronted in a dramatic way by the holiness of God,

11:49.154 --> 11:56.582
He is the prophet of God, set apart to the privilege of proclaiming the good news of God and calling people to account.

11:57.022 --> 11:59.044
And when God confronts him, what does he say?

11:59.785 --> 12:02.287
I am a man of unclean lips.

12:03.709 --> 12:16.562
That the mechanism that God has raised up for usefulness becomes the real temptation to use it in a way that is unpalatable.

12:18.754 --> 12:31.952
when all that we say in a single day with never a word left out, were printed each night in clear black and white, it would make strange reading, no doubt.

12:33.134 --> 12:39.523
And then just suppose, air our eyes should close, we must read the whole record through.

12:39.563 --> 12:47.314
Then wouldn't we sigh, and wouldn't we try a great deal less talking to do?

12:48.226 --> 12:58.858
And I more than half think that many a king that is many a king in life's tangle thread.

13:02.682 --> 13:04.664
How can I not remember that?

13:04.684 --> 13:14.315
And I more than half think that many a king would be smoother in life's tangle thread.

13:15.837 --> 13:17.138
If all that I say

13:17.986 --> 13:25.735
in a single day where to be left forever on set.

13:25.755 --> 13:35.107
You remember Wesley's thing, every day do all the good you can to all the people you can with all the means you have and so on.

13:35.728 --> 13:47.602
It's so easy to start out in a morning like that and to discover that you haven't made it to 11 o'clock and you are already in difficulty.

13:48.386 --> 13:56.596
in the area of greatest gift were confronted with the arena of the greatest potential for failure.

13:57.878 --> 14:00.261
Speech, conduct, or behavior.

14:01.302 --> 14:03.965
The false teachers were into conduct and into behavior.

14:04.346 --> 14:05.667
They had their own regulations.

14:05.707 --> 14:07.329
We saw that in verse 3.

14:08.631 --> 14:14.258
Your conduct says, Paul to Timothy, is to become like the Lord Jesus.

14:14.434 --> 14:28.168
Because after all, remember Paul writes in Romans and he says that the eternal purpose of God is that those he has predestined and called, it is in order that we might be conformed to the image of the Lord Jesus.

14:28.488 --> 14:33.633
When he writes to the second Corinthians, he says, and we are being transformed into his likeness.

14:33.994 --> 14:39.939
And when John writes in 1 John 3, he says, and when we see him, then we will be like him.

14:40.680 --> 14:42.482
But we're not quite like him yet.

14:43.298 --> 14:50.486
And some of us need to just check in with headquarters on this one.

14:51.127 --> 14:58.835
The father's desire for every one of us, irrespective of gifting, location, geography, age, anything.

14:58.855 --> 14:59.756
It's the same deal.

14:59.996 --> 15:06.183
He's doing the exact same with every single one of us, committed to making us like his son.

15:07.285 --> 15:08.206
That's what he's trying to do.

15:08.846 --> 15:09.807
Actually, that's what he's doing.

15:10.128 --> 15:10.909
He's not trying.

15:11.289 --> 15:12.210
We might be trying.

15:12.450 --> 15:13.552
In fact, we're very trying.

15:14.553 --> 15:24.248
So the father's desire and the father's design is that speech, conduct, very obvious in public life, right?

15:24.949 --> 15:26.091
Because people can hear what you say.

15:26.953 --> 15:28.275
They can see how you drive your car.

15:30.057 --> 15:31.920
There's nowhere to hide on that.

15:32.662 --> 15:34.044
But what about the next section?

15:35.045 --> 15:38.130
Love, faith, purity.

15:43.266 --> 15:46.890
Well, we could camp on any one of these, but we're not here for the rest of the day.

15:46.930 --> 15:50.293
He comes to this again, doesn't he?

15:50.874 --> 15:52.536
Particularly the last of these.

15:54.458 --> 15:58.942
Chapter five, don't rebuke an older man, but encourage him as you would a father.

15:59.002 --> 16:10.514
Younger men treat them as brothers, older women as mothers, younger women as sisters in all purity.

16:12.354 --> 16:18.862
He comes back to it again, still in chapter 5 says, don't be hasty in the laying on of hands, nor take part in the sins of others.

16:19.543 --> 16:23.788
Keep yourself pure, pure purity.

16:25.410 --> 16:29.114
Here's a quote, I don't know from whom, but I have it in my notes.

16:29.955 --> 16:41.970
How many false and failing ministers have misused secluded pastoral situations

16:42.562 --> 16:52.512
to embark on sexual adventures to the shipwreck of their ministries and to the shame of biblical Christianity.

16:54.333 --> 17:01.000
Well, of course, we don't want to pause on Julie on this, but we need to take it to heart.

17:02.842 --> 17:08.327
You know, when you're young, you imagine that one day you will be old.

17:09.448 --> 17:11.410
If you live long enough, you will be old.

17:12.258 --> 17:15.622
You can be like me in your 70s.

17:16.563 --> 17:21.709
And if you're young, you may think, as I thought when I was the age you are, it must be great.

17:21.769 --> 17:24.052
You get to 70 and all that stuff.

17:24.432 --> 17:29.178
You know, the passions of youth, power, possessions, all these things.

17:29.618 --> 17:31.581
They'll all be in the background.

17:31.601 --> 17:32.321
Not for a moment.

17:32.942 --> 17:34.504
Not for a moment.

17:34.524 --> 17:36.306
No.

17:36.418 --> 17:43.728
The Westminster Confession is helpful when it says, the Christian is engaged in a continual and irreconcilable war.

17:44.529 --> 17:46.131
A continual and irreconcilable war.

17:46.412 --> 17:52.841
It is a war that has been won in Christ, but it is a war that we are waging all day, every day.

17:52.861 --> 17:58.989
And let the person who thinks he stands, take heed, lest he falls.

17:59.810 --> 18:02.053
Temptation is no respect or of style.

18:04.016 --> 18:05.618
The disasters

18:05.826 --> 18:34.514
in the years of my life have been disasters amongst some flamboyant people and some of the most unlikely people that you would ever imagine, some of the stiffest, starchy, old Presbyterian types who took their own life when they discovered that the community had discovered their multiple adulteries over a long period of time.

18:34.946 --> 18:43.038
while they were some of the most effective preachers and conference speakers in the entire Western world.

18:44.280 --> 18:47.766
We are naive at best if we fiddle with this.

18:49.729 --> 18:50.991
What is the antidote to it?

18:53.194 --> 18:55.177
Well, the antidote to it is first of all, the wife.

18:55.858 --> 18:56.920
That really helps.

18:57.661 --> 19:01.106
And that's why God put the marriage thing together.

19:01.602 --> 19:11.252
That's why it's virtually impossible to deal with Roman Catholicism without acknowledging what a manifold disaster that has been, and we'll leave that aside for now.

19:11.953 --> 19:31.154
But Charles Bridges, if you remember old Charles Bridges, not Jerry Bridges, Charles Bridges, Charles Bridges says that tender, well-regulated domestic affection is the best defense against the vagrant desires of

19:32.674 --> 19:37.081
carnal passions.

19:37.101 --> 19:40.045
It takes a puritan to come out with that, but it's very good.

19:40.846 --> 19:49.900
So I would speak at a conference and somebody would ask a question about, what about you go to the conference and you've got here, you stay in the hotel and you do the thing and everything else.

19:50.721 --> 19:52.744
I said, well, this is what Bridges said.

19:53.205 --> 20:02.258
He said that the best antidote to the kind of stupidity you're talking about is tender, well-regulated domestic affection.

20:02.722 --> 20:12.174
And as soon as I get finished with this conference, then I'm going home for some tender, well-regulated, domestic affection.

20:12.795 --> 20:14.096
And that's the answer.

20:14.136 --> 20:15.378
That is the answer.

20:15.438 --> 20:20.104
Half of the situations that have emerged are twofold.

20:20.324 --> 20:28.474
One, because husbands do not fulfill the responsibility that God has entrusted them, and they deal with wives along the way.

20:28.514 --> 20:31.378
And then you add to that pride.

20:31.874 --> 20:37.821
And as soon as the pride thing takes over, it's a slow train coming.

20:38.462 --> 20:44.209
I mentioned earlier the trilogy by Cicero.

20:44.850 --> 21:01.490
And one of the great illustrations of this in that book, incidentally, these little moleskin things, they're both a delight and a challenge because I can never find anything in them.

21:01.634 --> 21:13.807
Crassus, who is an opponent of Cicero, knows that if he can get Cicero to succumb to his seductive ideas, he will gain triumph over him.

21:14.428 --> 21:25.500
And so now remember, it is the slave Tyro who is recording this incident.

21:26.421 --> 21:30.866
In response to insincere flattery from Crassus,

21:31.042 --> 21:34.907
who comes and says all these things in flattery.

21:36.569 --> 21:45.319
Tiro observes, there was a time when Cicero would have spotted such an obvious trap, a mile off.

21:46.741 --> 22:00.978
But I fear there is in all men who achieve their life's ambition, only a narrow line between dignity and vanity, confidence

22:01.186 --> 22:05.430
and delusion, glory, and self-destruction.

22:06.872 --> 22:21.306
Instead of staying in his seat and modestly disavowing such praise, Cicero rose and made a long speech agreeing with Cressus' every word.

22:22.047 --> 22:26.751
And that is a turning point in the story of Cicero in that Roman trilogy.

22:27.352 --> 22:28.053
It was pride.

22:28.673 --> 22:29.394
It was pride.

22:29.730 --> 22:35.756
Every moral disaster in all the time I've been here may be traced to one place.

22:36.096 --> 22:37.497
Pride is pride.

22:37.758 --> 22:40.700
It doesn't matter if it's sex, money, bullying, whatever else it is.

22:41.561 --> 22:54.113
The idea is that somehow or another, the individual has been seduced by the idea that he no longer lives under the jurisdiction of these things.

22:54.854 --> 22:57.516
It would be wrong of me to give you chapter and verse.

22:58.477 --> 22:59.378
I wouldn't need to.

23:00.930 --> 23:06.900
So he says these things about his character, and then he urges him in relationship to his work.

23:08.562 --> 23:14.712
And these are the convictions, of course, that really give rise to our even coming together today, I think.

23:15.594 --> 23:20.682
Timothy is to devote himself, and notice the imperative nature of these things.

23:21.203 --> 23:28.114
I mean, what Paul is really saying is, Timothy, become what you are by the power of God

23:28.258 --> 23:31.963
so that you and everybody else might see what God is doing with your life.

23:32.564 --> 23:42.719
So that the imperatives that to-do's come on now are on the basis of God's grace to him, in him, and through him.

23:43.420 --> 23:48.687
Now, Timothy, I want you to become the child of God that God has made you to be.

23:48.767 --> 23:56.178
Become what you are by the power of God so that it will become apparent to you and everybody else.

23:57.730 --> 24:02.635
Don't neglect, practice, immerse, watch.

24:05.958 --> 24:11.083
Work out your own salvation, essentially, as he says elsewhere, with fear and trembling.

24:14.386 --> 24:17.049
Devote yourself to the public reading of Scripture.

24:18.210 --> 24:20.112
It's hard to know what that actually meant, isn't it?

24:20.432 --> 24:26.738
Although we know that they read the law of God in the synagogue

24:27.106 --> 24:32.033
And so the public reading of the law was part and parcel of what was taking place.

24:32.814 --> 24:38.482
And presumably going on and beyond that, the reading out of letter such as this would be there.

24:40.965 --> 24:53.042
Justin Martyr records the century time on the day called Sunday, all who live in cities or in the country gather together in one place.

24:53.346 --> 24:59.632
And the memoirs of the apostles and the writings of the prophets are read as long as time permits.

25:00.252 --> 25:06.178
Then when the reader is finished, the president speaks, instructing and exhorting the people.

25:06.779 --> 25:11.263
So what Paul is urging to take place here was clearly happening.

25:13.785 --> 25:16.828
Just a brief comment on the public reading of Scripture.

25:18.229 --> 25:23.314
Not only is he urging that Scripture will be read,

25:24.066 --> 25:27.170
but also presumably urging what would be read?

25:27.950 --> 25:39.183
Because if you think about the opening five verses and the intriguing notions of genealogies and myths and all kinds of things, there's little doubt that some of them said, why don't we read some of those old genealogies?

25:39.223 --> 25:45.010
Because that would be good fodder for being able to promulgate various ideas and so on.

25:45.891 --> 25:52.338
But not only the reading of itself and the content of the reading, but how the reading is done.

25:53.506 --> 26:00.013
Can I just put in a plea for you guys to read the Bible in the public arena with your congregation?

26:06.721 --> 26:07.502
Let me tell you something.

26:07.522 --> 26:09.004
You'll never hear your grandchildren say.

26:09.064 --> 26:13.729
You'll never hear grandchildren say, let's go up in the attic and read grandpa's emails.

26:14.790 --> 26:15.331
It won't happen.

26:16.172 --> 26:17.213
They won't read your emails.

26:18.094 --> 26:19.175
They may read your notes.

