You see that all is of your concern.

48:40.820 --> 48:45.906
All things are for your sakes, as the apostle says in another case.

48:46.882 --> 48:49.286
Then only I entreat you.

48:50.127 --> 48:52.030
One, pity us.

48:52.771 --> 48:57.558
We are not angels, but men of light passions with yourselves.

48:58.539 --> 49:01.343
Before of charity, then of censure.

49:02.385 --> 49:10.877
We have all that you have to do about the saving of our own souls, and a great work besides about the saving of yours.

49:11.698 --> 49:14.322
We have all your difficulties as Christians,

49:14.818 --> 49:21.885
and some that you are not acquainted with, that are only ministers, temptations, and trials.

49:22.365 --> 49:34.176
That's why being together as food soldiers is such a help, because the only person that can really get to where we really live our lives is another fellow food soldier, they know.

49:34.196 --> 49:35.918
We're in the trenches, we get this.

49:36.318 --> 49:39.681
Where there's friendly fire coming at us from 15 directions.

49:40.142 --> 49:42.985
And so he's telling the congregation, you should pity us.

49:43.785 --> 49:44.466
Secondly,

49:44.642 --> 49:46.484
Help us in our work.

49:47.145 --> 49:51.071
If you can do anything, help us in the work of winning souls.

49:51.972 --> 49:53.434
What can we do, say you?

49:53.454 --> 49:55.997
Oh, a great deal.

49:56.037 --> 50:02.566
Be but one in Christ, and we are made.

50:03.247 --> 50:10.937
Make haste to heaven, that you and we may joyfully meet before the throne of God and the Lamb.

50:12.480 --> 50:14.322
Pity us, help us,

50:14.914 --> 50:21.901
pray for us, how often and how eagerly doth Paul beg the prayers of the churches.

50:22.982 --> 50:26.926
And if he did so, much more should we beg them.

50:28.267 --> 50:35.153
And you grant them, for our necessities and weaknesses are greater than Paul's.

50:36.695 --> 50:44.082
He said, finally, brethren, pray for us, that the word of the Lord may have free course and be glorified

50:44.386 --> 50:55.783
even as it is with you, and that we may be delivered from unreasonable and wicked men, for all men have not faith.

50:58.166 --> 51:03.654
So if someone in your congregation says, so how did the thing go?

51:03.694 --> 51:05.878
You say, well, some of it was pretty good.

51:06.298 --> 51:07.260
We got a lot of books.

51:07.660 --> 51:11.666
They were giving books away.

51:12.194 --> 51:23.728
The fellow that was talking said that you as a member of the congregation should pity me, should help me, and should pray for me.

51:27.753 --> 51:28.414
Well, let's pray.

51:32.479 --> 51:34.881
Lord, these things are above us and beyond us.

51:36.223 --> 51:41.970
Even the things that we have briefly pondered

51:42.786 --> 51:44.868
speak to the very core of our being.

51:46.029 --> 51:48.632
And we bow before you as a group of men.

51:48.692 --> 51:51.475
Our lives are an open book to you.

51:51.495 --> 51:55.499
There are no secret places before you that live in God.

51:56.680 --> 52:10.834
And so we ask that by the Holy Spirit, where a word of encouragement has come with useful effectiveness, that it may stir us up and set us on our feet.

52:11.586 --> 52:22.561
And we're a word of rebuke or correction has come that it may cast us down before you so that we might cry out for forgiveness and for grace.

52:23.562 --> 52:41.426
And we pray that as we walk out into the remainder of this day and this week together, that as faces and names come to mind, that we might earnestly pray for one another as we seek to contend for the faith

52:41.730 --> 52:44.195
that has been once for all delivered to the saints.

52:45.357 --> 52:53.433
And we commend one another, and our wives, and our children, and our loved ones, and our church congregations to you.

52:54.174 --> 52:55.858
And we pray in Jesus' name.

53:01.248 --> 53:04.114
Amen.

53:04.226 --> 53:11.942
and you're welcome to pass this sermon along to others, but please don't charge for it or alter it without written permission from Truth For Life.

